body:
Hi all, i just finished my first game with Gnar.... humiliatingly going 1/10/4. Against a riven. That wasn&#039;t even level 30. 
So i think you can imagine i was ready to down some chlorax after that game and it felt pretty bad because i felt so helpless in lane, if i tried to towerfarm, she&#039;d just towerdive and i&#039;d be down in 3 seconds flat. It tilted me a lot.
PLease tell me how to play gnar because i am absolutely clueless. All advice will be duly Appreciated. {{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}

replies.body:
Due to his deceptive range and low health pool, Gnar is actually somewhat weakish in the really early game, his 'range' makes you feel stronger and people tend to overextend, I would say play safe early and the rest of the game should be fine :P

